18
00:00:12,331 --> 00:00:15,331
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:17,355 --> 00:00:19,232
<i>Battle for Ringo Vinda.</i>

20
00:00:19,316 --> 00:00:23,153
<i>Republic forces are locked in
heated combat with the droid armada</i>

21
00:00:23,236 --> 00:00:27,115
<i>on a massive space station
that encircles an entire planet.</i>

22
00:00:27,199 --> 00:00:30,619
<i>Anakin Skywalker valiantly
leads his men against the onslaught,</i>

23
00:00:30,702 --> 00:00:35,373
<i>which has lasted several rotations,
with neither side gaining any ground.</i>

24
00:00:35,457 --> 00:00:39,044
<i>Aided by the twin sister Jedi Masters,
Tiplee and Tiplar,</i>

25
00:00:39,127 --> 00:00:41,504
<i>the Republic now mounts
a desperate offensive</i>

26
00:00:41,588 --> 00:00:43,131
<i>to break the deadlock.</i>

27
00:00:50,347 --> 00:00:51,848
Push forward!

28
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,266
Stay to my left.

29
00:00:54,226 --> 00:00:55,477
Fives! Watch out!

30
00:00:58,355 --> 00:01:00,690
Thanks, brother, I owe you one.

31
00:01:00,774 --> 00:01:03,109
You owe me a lot more than one.

32
00:01:14,663 --> 00:01:15,956
Tighten our flank!

33
00:01:21,795 --> 00:01:23,672
-Shields up!
-Yes, sir!

34
00:01:48,238 --> 00:01:51,616
Don't get too comfortable.
This battle hasn't been won yet.

35
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:55,203
Master Skywalker,
we must get to the command post.

36
00:01:55,287 --> 00:01:57,247
Admiral Trench has sent
for reinforcements.

37
00:01:57,330 --> 00:01:59,666
We must take this post
before they arrive.

38
00:02:01,626 --> 00:02:04,754
It's time for phase two.
We're at this position.

39
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:07,215
Tiplar, you'll take your men
down this passageway.

40
00:02:07,299 --> 00:02:09,050
Tiplee, you'll move along here.

41
00:02:09,384 --> 00:02:11,177
They'll have to divide their forces
to counter us.

42
00:02:11,261 --> 00:02:13,555
And when they do,
Rex and I will press through the middle.

43
00:02:13,638 --> 00:02:16,850
If we time it right, we'll all converge
on this spot at the same time,

44
00:02:16,933 --> 00:02:18,184
and the droids won't know
what hit them.

45
00:02:18,268 --> 00:02:20,895
If we're making a run,
we'll need backup.

46
00:02:20,979 --> 00:02:22,897
My men are severely depleted.

47
00:02:23,481 --> 00:02:25,942
Fives, you and Tup take
ten of your best men

48
00:02:26,026 --> 00:02:27,485
and support Master Tiplar.

49
00:02:27,569 --> 00:02:28,862
We're on it, sir.

50
00:02:31,531 --> 00:02:32,949
Hey, you all right?

51
00:02:33,033 --> 00:02:35,160
Yeah, I... I just...

52
00:02:35,243 --> 00:02:36,911
Come on, this is a textbook battle.

53
00:02:37,037 --> 00:02:39,664
We've run through this
a million times before in training.

54
00:02:39,748 --> 00:02:44,461
Yeah, I know... I just...
I don't feel like myself.

55
00:02:44,544 --> 00:02:46,212
What do you mean?

56
00:02:49,215 --> 00:02:50,550
Follow me.

57
00:02:51,092 --> 00:02:52,761
Jedi.

58
00:02:52,886 --> 00:02:55,055
Tup? What's the matter with you?

59
00:02:55,722 --> 00:02:57,682
No... Nothing. I'm fine.

60
00:02:57,766 --> 00:03:00,852
Come on, brother.
Don't want to be left behind.

61
00:03:35,136 --> 00:03:39,307
Increase our defenses.
We must hold them here.

62
00:03:55,323 --> 00:03:57,617
Don't fall back! Push forward!

63
00:04:00,245 --> 00:04:03,123
Tup! Hey!
This is not the time to freeze up!

64
00:04:03,206 --> 00:04:06,418
Pull it together! We're almost
to the finish line! Come on!

65
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:22,225
Jedi...

66
00:04:24,727 --> 00:04:26,855
Good soldiers follow orders.

67
00:04:27,647 --> 00:04:28,690
Hey, Tup!

68
00:04:29,232 --> 00:04:30,525
On your right!

69
00:04:33,027 --> 00:04:34,195
Tup! No!

70
00:04:36,281 --> 00:04:37,323
Sister!

71
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,001
Hold your position!

72
00:04:51,671 --> 00:04:52,922
Destroyers!

73
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:01,723
We've lost our momentum ! Fall back!

74
00:05:05,602 --> 00:05:07,437
Fives, I don't know what's going on,

75
00:05:07,562 --> 00:05:11,065
but you are responsible for Tup now.
Get him back to base. I want answers.

76
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:40,345
The Jedi have withdrawn their forces.

77
00:05:40,428 --> 00:05:43,097
Contact Count Dooku immediately.

78
00:05:45,099 --> 00:05:48,811
I have something
he'll be very interested in.

79
00:05:54,901 --> 00:05:59,656
Count Dooku,
the Republic forces are in full retreat.

80
00:06:00,448 --> 00:06:03,785
<i>But this is not why
you have contacted me, is it?</i>

81
00:06:04,244 --> 00:06:10,208
No, Count, in truth the Republic had
pushed my droids to the breaking point,

82
00:06:10,291 --> 00:06:13,253
when they suddenly turned
and fell back.

83
00:06:14,504 --> 00:06:16,923
It seemed that
at the height of the conflict,

84
00:06:17,006 --> 00:06:20,802
a clone turned on his Jedi General

85
00:06:22,011 --> 00:06:23,805
and executed her.

86
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:25,974
<i>Intentionally?</i>

87
00:06:26,558 --> 00:06:28,935
I saw it with my own eyes.

88
00:06:29,018 --> 00:06:32,897
I have studied clones and fought
against them in many battles.

89
00:06:32,981 --> 00:06:39,821
This action is unlike anything I have
witnessed in their behavior as soldiers.

90
00:06:39,904 --> 00:06:42,740
<i>So, there is a traitor in their midst.</i>

91
00:06:42,824 --> 00:06:46,828
<i>It's rare, but such things
have been reported in the past.</i>

92
00:06:48,413 --> 00:06:53,167
Not a traitor, this was different.
It seemed...

93
00:06:53,251 --> 00:06:54,794
<i>Yes, Admiral?</i>

94
00:06:54,877 --> 00:06:58,881
It seemed as if the clone
could not help himself,

95
00:06:58,965 --> 00:07:02,010
as if he was entranced.

96
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:06,306
<i>Thank you, Admiral.
I will take this under advisement.</i>

97
00:07:24,032 --> 00:07:26,659
Why? Why would he do this?

98
00:07:27,368 --> 00:07:29,203
I'm about to find out.

99
00:07:31,956 --> 00:07:33,166
How's he doing, Rex?

100
00:07:33,249 --> 00:07:37,712
I'm not sure, General.
It seems like he just snapped.

101
00:07:39,964 --> 00:07:41,883
Tup, can you hear me?

102
00:07:42,008 --> 00:07:44,677
-Yes, Captain.
-What happened?

103
00:07:44,761 --> 00:07:46,054
What do you mean?

104
00:07:46,137 --> 00:07:48,806
Do you have any idea
what you've done?

105
00:07:49,432 --> 00:07:53,227
Good soldiers follow orders.
Good soldiers follow orders.

106
00:07:53,311 --> 00:07:57,023
Good soldiers follow orders.
Good soldiers follow orders.

107
00:08:02,153 --> 00:08:04,155
What is he talking about?

108
00:08:04,238 --> 00:08:05,657
I have no idea.

109
00:08:17,335 --> 00:08:19,379
Kill the Jedi.

110
00:08:27,887 --> 00:08:29,347
We have to get him back
to the medical bay

111
00:08:29,430 --> 00:08:31,766
before he hurts anyone else.

112
00:08:40,775 --> 00:08:45,196
My Lord, I have received a report
that leads me to conclude

113
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:48,449
we may have encountered
a grave complication

114
00:08:48,574 --> 00:08:50,284
with one of our assets.

115
00:08:50,368 --> 00:08:51,661
<i>Assets?</i>

116
00:08:51,744 --> 00:08:56,708
Yes, sir. A clone trooper has
executed one of the Jedi Generals.

117
00:08:56,791 --> 00:09:00,878
<i>And you believe this is indicative
of our programming?</i>

118
00:09:00,962 --> 00:09:05,133
I do, My Lord. But I cannot be certain.

119
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:09,637
<i>It is pertinent we ascertain
if this is an isolated event,</i>

120
00:09:10,096 --> 00:09:13,891
<i>a failure in this particular
clone's programming.</i>

121
00:09:13,975 --> 00:09:17,478
<i>Otherwise my plans may be ruined.</i>

122
00:09:17,645 --> 00:09:20,815
<i>Seize the clone immediately.</i>

123
00:09:20,898 --> 00:09:22,984
Yes, My Master.

124
00:09:33,327 --> 00:09:36,622
Fives, what's happening to me?

125
00:09:37,248 --> 00:09:39,333
You don't remember?

126
00:09:40,001 --> 00:09:41,252
No.

127
00:09:41,377 --> 00:09:43,671
You murdered General Tiplar.

128
00:09:43,755 --> 00:09:47,592
What? No, that's not possible.

129
00:09:47,675 --> 00:09:52,180
I would never... I could never...

130
00:09:52,263 --> 00:09:53,681
Tup, you did.

131
00:09:53,765 --> 00:09:57,393
I don't... I don't understand.
How could this happen?

132
00:09:57,727 --> 00:09:59,228
What's happening to me, Fives?

133
00:10:00,688 --> 00:10:03,191
No! No! No...

134
00:10:09,739 --> 00:10:11,449
What do you think happened?

135
00:10:11,532 --> 00:10:13,284
Did you check all of his scans?

136
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:16,287
Well, all of his scans are clear.

137
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:19,290
As far as I can tell,
this is a combat-related stress.

138
00:10:19,373 --> 00:10:21,876
It's seems he's had
some sort of breakdown.

139
00:10:22,418 --> 00:10:23,961
Kix, you should know better.

140
00:10:24,045 --> 00:10:26,631
We were designed
to withstand any stress.

141
00:10:26,839 --> 00:10:30,343
I agree.
We've been through a lot together.

142
00:10:30,426 --> 00:10:32,345
He doesn't seem
to remember what happened.

143
00:10:32,428 --> 00:10:34,889
It's like he's sick, or drugged.

144
00:10:34,972 --> 00:10:39,602
Well, it could be a virus, a toxin.

145
00:10:39,685 --> 00:10:41,562
I can't be certain.

146
00:10:41,646 --> 00:10:43,731
Let's talk outside.

147
00:10:47,235 --> 00:10:50,363
You mean the enemy could have
made him do this?

148
00:10:50,446 --> 00:10:51,656
It's a possibility.

149
00:10:51,739 --> 00:10:54,492
There have been rumors
that Separatists have been trying

150
00:10:54,575 --> 00:10:58,704
to develop an anti-clone virus.
Biological warfare.

151
00:10:58,830 --> 00:11:02,124
Listen, we aren't equipped
for this type of situation.

152
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:07,296
He'll have to be taken back to Kamino.
Only then will you have your answer.

153
00:11:11,217 --> 00:11:12,760
Wait! Wait!

154
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:18,307
Tup, it's gonna be fine. I promise.

155
00:11:18,391 --> 00:11:20,101
They'll fix you up real good.

156
00:11:20,184 --> 00:11:22,353
We'll be having
a drink together in no time, eh?

157
00:11:22,436 --> 00:11:25,398
Good soldiers follow orders.

158
00:11:25,481 --> 00:11:28,192
Good soldiers follow orders.

159
00:11:28,276 --> 00:11:29,652
You are a good soldier, Tup.

160
00:11:29,735 --> 00:11:31,529
It's time to go now.

161
00:11:32,697 --> 00:11:34,115
Be careful.

162
00:11:34,365 --> 00:11:35,867
Yes, General.

163
00:12:14,155 --> 00:12:19,243
We are tracking clean, calculating
hyperspace jump in five, four...

164
00:12:19,327 --> 00:12:20,828
Wait! Wait!

165
00:12:20,912 --> 00:12:23,331
Scanners indicate incoming craft.
Abort jump!

166
00:12:57,698 --> 00:13:00,618
Mayday! Mayday!
The enemy cut us off!

167
00:13:00,701 --> 00:13:02,536
They must have
circled around behind us.

168
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:04,038
We're being overwhelmed.

169
00:13:35,319 --> 00:13:37,279
Can't let 'em in here! Hold that line.

170
00:13:42,493 --> 00:13:43,744
Here they come.

171
00:13:45,413 --> 00:13:46,664
Blast them!

172
00:14:42,553 --> 00:14:43,679
General Skywalker,

173
00:14:43,763 --> 00:14:46,557
you are nearing the coordinates
where we lost contact with the shuttle.

174
00:14:46,640 --> 00:14:50,227
<i>We can see it now.
It doesn't look good.</i>

175
00:14:57,568 --> 00:15:00,988
Looks like some buzz droids got on
the hull and opened her right up.

176
00:15:01,947 --> 00:15:05,034
Strategically, this attack
doesn't make any sense.

177
00:15:05,159 --> 00:15:08,162
Unless they were
after something specific.

178
00:15:08,245 --> 00:15:10,247
-Tup...
-I'm going over there.

179
00:15:10,331 --> 00:15:11,749
We're coming with you.

180
00:15:39,193 --> 00:15:41,570
Over here. This is Tup's gurney.

181
00:15:44,698 --> 00:15:46,909
The restraints have been cut.

182
00:15:47,868 --> 00:15:50,663
The clankers took Tup? Why?

183
00:15:50,746 --> 00:15:54,041
They must be responsible
for whatever's happening to him.

184
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:55,251
It's possible.

185
00:15:55,334 --> 00:15:57,962
All I know is they went to great lengths
to capture him.

186
00:15:58,045 --> 00:15:59,296
And that means something.

187
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:01,215
We have got to get him back.

188
00:16:01,715 --> 00:16:04,301
Don't worry. We'll find a way.

189
00:16:09,890 --> 00:16:12,434
We have captured the clone, Count.

190
00:16:12,935 --> 00:16:14,395
<i>Good work, Admiral.</i>

191
00:16:14,478 --> 00:16:16,355
<i>Send him to me immediately,</i>

192
00:16:16,438 --> 00:16:19,859
<i>and under all circumstances,
keep him alive!</i>

193
00:16:20,818 --> 00:16:22,111
Yes, sir.

194
00:16:23,571 --> 00:16:26,365
Get him on the next shuttle out of here.

195
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:28,826
But the Republic blockade...

196
00:16:28,909 --> 00:16:31,495
See to it personally, Commander.

197
00:16:44,842 --> 00:16:46,510
It will be just the three of us going in.

198
00:16:46,594 --> 00:16:48,888
The shuttle will drop us off
just short of the main hanger,

199
00:16:48,971 --> 00:16:50,681
then we spacewalk from there.

200
00:16:50,764 --> 00:16:52,516
Are you picking anything up
on Tup's locator?

201
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,895
I've got a faint signal,
but it's hard to track. It's moving.

202
00:16:56,645 --> 00:16:57,897
Then we better hurry.

203
00:17:35,809 --> 00:17:39,271
I've got a better signal.
Tup is heading this way.

204
00:17:39,563 --> 00:17:41,941
They're moving him to the hangar.

205
00:18:11,595 --> 00:18:14,932
Are your scopes Jedi-issue, sir?

206
00:18:15,557 --> 00:18:17,351
Stay focused, Fives.

207
00:18:22,731 --> 00:18:25,734
-There he is, sir.
-We'll have to work fast.

208
00:18:25,859 --> 00:18:28,112
There must be a hundred droids
in that hangar,

209
00:18:28,195 --> 00:18:29,780
not to mention the star fighters.

210
00:18:29,863 --> 00:18:32,199
This is stretching it, even for you, sir!

211
00:18:32,283 --> 00:18:34,410
Rex, you're beginning
to sound like Obi-Wan.

212
00:18:34,493 --> 00:18:36,120
You got a better idea?

213
00:18:36,203 --> 00:18:38,747
Look, I don't doubt you could pull it off,

214
00:18:38,831 --> 00:18:42,376
but I'm just not sure Fives and I
would be around to see it happen.

215
00:18:42,459 --> 00:18:44,920
-I've got an idea.
-Well, let's hear it, quickly!

216
00:18:46,797 --> 00:18:48,549
Grappling gun. Good thinking.

217
00:18:48,966 --> 00:18:50,259
Get ready to hold on.

218
00:18:50,342 --> 00:18:53,679
That's why he's the ARC Trooper.

219
00:19:19,496 --> 00:19:21,081
Is there a problem?

220
00:19:21,165 --> 00:19:25,753
We were experiencing some drag
but the sensors are stabilized now.

221
00:19:25,836 --> 00:19:29,548
You were experiencing drag
in the vacuum of space?

222
00:19:29,715 --> 00:19:32,885
Yeah, strange. But it is gone now.

223
00:19:46,774 --> 00:19:48,359
Scrap them!

224
00:20:12,299 --> 00:20:15,177
Hey, now we're
experiencing turbulence.

225
00:20:16,136 --> 00:20:18,889
What's going on?
What do you know about this clone?

226
00:20:19,598 --> 00:20:21,892
I am programmed to resist intimidation.

227
00:20:22,518 --> 00:20:23,644
Fine.

228
00:20:29,650 --> 00:20:31,151
How's he doing?

229
00:20:31,235 --> 00:20:33,821
Not well. Not well at all.

230
00:20:33,904 --> 00:20:35,906
I think he's dying, sir.

231
00:20:36,198 --> 00:20:38,409
We have to get him to Kamino.

232
00:20:57,553 --> 00:20:59,763
I'll want a full report from Kamino.

233
00:20:59,847 --> 00:21:02,224
If Tup is the victim
of some Separatist plot,

234
00:21:02,307 --> 00:21:06,186
we have no idea
of how widespread it already is.

235
00:21:06,937 --> 00:21:08,730
Permission to come with you, sir.

236
00:21:08,814 --> 00:21:12,025
He's my best friend.
You may need help.

237
00:21:12,109 --> 00:21:14,778
But everything must be done
by the book.

238
00:21:14,862 --> 00:21:16,029
Understood, sir.

239
00:21:16,113 --> 00:21:21,201
You're to stay by his side at all times.
I don't want any more slip-ups.

240
00:21:21,326 --> 00:21:23,871
-Yes, sir.
-Good. Let's go.

241
00:21:40,888 --> 00:21:44,808
<i>Medical frigate 517,
you are cleared for departure.</i>

242
00:21:45,476 --> 00:21:47,394
Good luck, boys.

243
00:21:47,418 --> 00:21:52,418
http://hiqve.com/

